---

## ENGINE CLASSES — MUST BE PURE FUNCTIONS

AdaptiveTDEEEngine, EffortScoreCalculator, and MacroTargetCalculator
MUST be pure — same inputs always produce same outputs. No side effects.
No HealthKit calls, no SwiftData queries, no network calls inside Engine/.
Pass all required data in as parameters. This makes them trivially testable.

Example:
✅ func calculate(samples: [HRSample], age: Int) -> EffortLevel
❌ func calculate() -> EffortLevel  // fetches data internally — WRONG

---

## TESTING RULES

- Every function in Engine/ MUST have a corresponding unit test
- Tests live in EngineTests/ and use XCTest
- Test file naming: [ClassName]Tests.swift
- Test function naming: test_[functionName]_[scenario]_[expectedResult]
- Example: test_calculateEffort_highHRZones_returnsHighLevel()
- Always write tests alongside the implementation — not after

---

## EXTERNAL APIs

### Nutritionix
- Base URL: https://trackapi.nutritionix.com/v2
- Auth headers: x-app-id and x-app-key (from Keychain)
- Endpoints used: /search/instant, /search/item (barcode), /natural/nutrients
- Always handle 429 rate limit errors gracefully with user-visible message

### Anthropic Claude API  
- Base URL: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages
- Auth header: x-api-key (from Keychain)
- Model: claude-sonnet-4-6 (latest capable model, good cost/quality balance)
- Always set max_tokens: 1000 for food extraction, 2000 for chat
- Food extraction calls: instruct to return ONLY valid JSON, no preamble
- Chat calls: inject today's macro summary as system context
- Always validate JSON response before parsing — never force unwrap

### Error Handling for APIs
- Network errors: show non-blocking toast, do not crash
- 401 errors: prompt user to re-enter API key
- 429 errors: show "try again in a moment" message
- Malformed JSON from Claude: fall back to asking user to rephrase

---

## HEALTHKIT RULES

- Always check HKHealthStore.isHealthDataAvailable() before any query
- Request ONLY the permissions you actually use — do not over-request
- Wrap all HKQuery callbacks in withCheckedContinuation for async/await compatibility
- Handle the case where user denies permission gracefully — app should still work without HealthKit, just without effort scoring
- Never cache HealthKit data in SwiftData — always re-query for fresh data
- Heart rate samples: query in 1-hour buckets for performance

---

## JAVA DEVELOPER REMINDERS

When you see Swift patterns that have Java equivalents, note them:

| Swift | Java equivalent |
|-------|----------------|
| protocol | interface |
| struct | class with value semantics (like a record) |
| enum with associated values | sealed class hierarchy |
| guard let x = y else { return } | if (y == null) return; |
| @State var x = 0 | private int x = 0; with a listener |
| @Query var entries | @LiveData / reactive JPA query |
| async/await | CompletableFuture / virtual threads |
| [T] | List<T> |
| [K:V] | Map<K,V> |
| T? | Optional<T> / nullable |
| ?? | orElse() |

---

## MANUAL FOOD ENTRY RULES

- Manual entry is always the fallback when barcode 404s or search returns empty
- Before showing a blank form, try Nutritionix /v2/natural/nutrients with the search
  query OR ask Claude to prefill estimates — pre-filled is better UX than blank
- If AI prefills the form, set confidence to .estimated UNLESS user edits the values,
  in which case set to .manual (user took ownership of the numbers)
- ManualFoodEntry saves to a persistent CustomFoodLibrary so the user can reuse it
- Custom foods appear in search results alongside Nutritionix results

---

## CUSTOM RECIPE RULES

- A Recipe stores ingredients as SNAPSHOTS of macros at save time, not live references
  Reason: if source food data changes, historical logs using the recipe stay accurate
- Recipes support serving scaling — always store total macros for the full batch
  and a defaultServings count; logging lets user pick how many servings they had
- Never mutate an existing recipe — create a new version instead
  Reason: FoodEntries that reference the old version should not be retroactively changed
- Recipe confidence = .recipe regardless of ingredient sources
- Recipes appear in the food search alongside Nutritionix results and custom foods
- Ingredient sources can be: Nutritionix result, CustomFood, or another Recipe (nested)
- Nested recipes max depth = 1 (a recipe can contain another recipe but not 3 levels deep)
  Reason: prevents circular references and keeps macro calculation simple

---

## WHAT TO DO WHEN STUCK

1. HealthKit query returning empty: check simulator has Health data (add some manually in the Health app)
2. SwiftData @Query not updating: make sure @Model class has @Observable or you're using @Query correctly
3. Xcode "No such module": clean build folder (Cmd+Shift+K) then rebuild
4. Simulator not showing camera: barcode scanner requires a real device — use a test barcode image on screen
5. Claude API returning malformed JSON: add explicit instruction in system prompt: "Return ONLY the JSON object. No markdown, no backticks, no explanation before or after."
6. HealthKit permissions not appearing: make sure HealthKit entitlement is enabled in project Signing & Capabilities tab
